text:
If you’re searching for the place where the prices are still reasonable and the quality of food together with the service are on the high level - this is exactly the place you want to go. Nice non-alcoholic drink; lemonade, tea AND Pineapple juice.. Coffee served in tiny cups. Difficult to get refills or water refills, but we did. Suggest an espresso machine, as Perfect addition. title: Park Chalet
text: We arrived at the restaurant 40 minutes earlier than our reservation, there were many tables available. The young female host(Andrea Tejeda) said we would have to wait until our reservation time, which was totally fine. But then, I noticed three parties who had reservations after ours being seated by this young female host, even the walked in customers were seated. I went to ask her, but she just continued talking to the people who had just come in and ignored me. Finally, I managed to ask her if our table was ready. She said I had to wait until our reservation time was up, and she continued leading the customers in without having them wait for their reservation time is up. By the time of our reservation, she still hadn't called us. At the same time, a party with a reservation 20 minutes later to our reservation arrived, which is not even their time yet! and she led them to a table immediately. How incredible and ridiculous is this?! If my family hadn't been very tired, we would've gone to another place that knows how to serve its customers. This place is nice, but it's terrible to have someone like this working here. I'm not sure she goes by race or other preferences to 'take care' of their customers.
name: X B.

title: Mixto Latin Cuisine
text: A gem in the Outer Sunset! I have tried some of their dishes and let me tell you Mixto never disappoints. I love the chicharrón de pollo and they also have really good birria tacos! The service was excellent and we also had a nice little chat with the owner who wanted to make sure everything was okay with our order. Definitely recommend this restaurant. textTranslated: I had a not pleasant experience, I am Peruvian and the Peruvian food that they prepare in that place does not represent anything to our gastronomy, ask for another menu less Peruvian food and you will be disappointed.

title: Mixto Latin Cuisine
text: Great service, friendly staff, DELICIOUS food! First time at Mixto and it did not disappoint. We went there for dinner and ordered ceviche mixto, birria taco’s and arroz con mariscos. The portions are very generous (two people couldn’t finish a starter, ceviche and a main, took some of it home) and everything is freshly made which makes them very flexible when it comes to food restrictions. I like the dim lighting because it made the dinner feel like date night on a Wednesday. Also, it is located in a quiet neighborhood which gives so much privacy and the time to properly enjoy your food without rushing to empty the table. Will visit them for brunch next time👌🏻

title: CreoLa
text:
Lovely neighborhood spot with delightful Louisiana cuisine in the Stanyan / Cole Valley area!
I'm vegetarian and Creole cuisine is always tricky because seemingly vegetarian dishes (e.g. rice & beans) often contain chicken stock or ham. CreoLA does a great job of creating vegetarian food that's authentic and not an afterthought. They have a vegetarian jambalaya that's amazing! The wild mushrooms in it are juicy and full of flavor and it makes me happy I can taste the beautiful flavors of Creole cooking. Also recommended are the hush puppies and the beignets. My partner loves the catfish here and says the fish is cooked just right and it's never over done.
name: Ramnath Balasubramanyan

Also, my friend’s portion was significantly bigger than mine making the situation funny. The place was packed with people without enough seats. They ask for a tip for all self-service and long wait time.

title: Hook Fish Co
text:
Been coming here for 7 years. Never been so abused as I have been on my most recent visit.

Walked in. There was no line. Great. No crowd meant that I knew I’d get my order soon. 30 minutes of waiting, I watched six people that arrived after me get served their food and start to leave. At that time I start complaining to the guy at the window… He’s just telling me you gotta wait up to another hour (because they got busy). I’m openly arguing with him and showing him the time of purchase… It’s only then he realizes that he’s in the wrong. Two minutes later a poke burrito shows up. - the burrito that gives me gastroenteritis six hours later.

I made an effort to drop them a private note on the back of their square receipt  (which asks for feedback), never heard back.

This place is milking all the Goodwill it earned during the pandemic. And I wouldn’t be surprised if it starts to collapse soon.
name: Michael Kukreja

title: Lemonade Restaurant
text:
My recent experience at Lemonade Restaurant left much to be desired, and various factors contributed to an overall lackluster visit. The food, including the chicken breast and salmon dishes, fell short of expectations, with a notable lack of flavor and a disappointingly dry texture. It was evident that the kitchen may have overlooked crucial elements that elevate a dining experience.

Adding to the disappointment was the sparse crowd; we were the only patrons at 7 pm on a Saturday night. This near-empty atmosphere was further highlighted by the visible departure of several potential diners who seemed unimpressed with the offerings. The lack of a bustling ambiance raised concerns about the restaurant's appeal and left us questioning our choice for the evening.

Unfortunately, the service didn't manage to salvage the experience. The servers appeared disinterested and failed to provide the helpful and attentive service one expects in a dining setting.

On a slightly positive note, the lemonade drinks offered a modest reprieve, providing a decent refreshment. However, they were not enough to counterbalance the subpar food and lackluster service.

In conclusion, Lemonade Restaurant's underwhelming food, poor service, and a conspicuously empty dining area on a Saturday night collectively painted a picture of an establishment struggling to meet expectations.
name: Andrew

title: Lemonade Restaurant
text: I stopped by last night in an effort to find some shelter from the rain. I was greeted by the duo working the front. They asked if I had any questions or would like to sample anything. I picked out my items and paid. Kudos to the young man who helped me out. I could tell he looked a bit tired but his smile never faded and he provided excellent service. Lovely place, amazing and genuine workers along with good food- what more could you ask for?
name: Alexander Stevens
responseFromOwnerText: Thank you so much for the great review, Alexander! Glad we could help get you out of the rain!

title: Lemonade Restaurant
text: Best lemonade here

responseFromOwnerText: Merci for the 5 Stars!  We appreciate your business and look forward to seeing you again soon!

title: Lemonade Restaurant
text: Good place
name: Khayotbek Tulkinjanov
responseFromOwnerText: We really appreciate you taking the time to leave us this great review!  We’re thankful you chose to dine at our café and we look forward to your next visit!

title: Lemonade Restaurant
text:
We came around 7:30pm but everything inside already was already cleaned up, with chairs up and floors wet, and all food trays put away. The closing time is supposed to be 9pm. This looks unprofessional to the customers walking in.

The photos and menu looks amazing but the reality is totally different. The guy who works here for sure he is not happy with his job/boss or he is having a bad day. No smile at all the whole time. He made me feel like me eating here is adding more work to his job, especially when he already cleaned up the whole restaurant 1.5 hour before closing time.
Food is served as cold even for meat like salmon/chicken unless you ASK for warm and the way they put the food together on the plate just like throwing everything inside to fill up the plate. You will be surprised by the server handing you the plate by ONE hand like don’t really care how you feel about their service.
I would give 0 star if I could for the quality of food and 00 for the service.
After the dinner I had to go somewhere to eat again because the portion for the price is not even fair.

title: Dragon River Restaurant
text:
February 2024:
Enjoyed a family dinner on a Thursday night. We pre-ordered the chicken stuffed with sticky rice. This dish is quite enjoyable because it's fried chicken stuffed with sticky rice that has a lot of delicious ingredients mixed in. This place did a good job.

Peking Duck was excellent. The skin was very crispy 😋. Fish fillet with asparagus was a Big hit too. Simple and cooked perfectly.

The white chicken with ginger sauce was another good dish.

Everything was tasty 😋. We ordered the pork belly taro clay pot dish that is an old time favorite and hard to find nowadays. Everyone enjoyed that too.

Overall, had a nice family dinner to celebrate Chinese New Year.
name: Ken Wong

title: Dragon River Restaurant
text: I’ve ordered our Chinese new year dinners from this restaurant for years and our friends and family rave about the food. The restaurant is family run and super friendly. I highly recommend the beef chow fun, whole steamed sea bass with ginger and scallion, Peking duck, dry braised string beans, mu shu chicken. They also have a sticky rice stuffed chicken dish that is famous (on my list to try). Order the steamed sea bass and sticky rice stuffed chicken dish 24 hours in advance.

responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Adele,
Thank you for taking the time to write this review. We certainly do miss Jorge, but after 38 years with us it was time for him to enjoy his life outside of work. We are the original owners since the beginning and we are disappointed to hear your experience was not what it once was. We certainly want you to enjoy your meal and if it’s ever underwhelming we are always happy to make it right. We hope you and your husband find yourselves here again so we can better serve you. 
Sincerely

responseFromOwnerText: Thank you!

title: Gold Coast Grill & Catering
text:
Was very underwhelmed by my experience, got a classic burger with fries, as well as tried options from the salad bar.

Obviously the most basic menu item, but the burger really left a lot to be desired, the meat tasted bland, dry, and overcooked, and the massive dry bun did it no favors. Hopefully the more complex menu items are better, because this was underwhelming for sure.

The salad bar ended up being pretty overpriced, I wanted to try their various pasta salads but with the weight price it ended up being $9 for a pretty small amount of food. I’m assuming this price is meant for customers to take the hot protein items like chicken tenders rather than just salads, but I found it too expensive.

Also there was no napkins available at the self service area for utensils as far as I could tell and that was awkward.

I’ll consider coming back but for $20 I really didn’t feel like the meal was worth it.
name: Ryan Winter (IWearCrocs)
responseFromOwnerText:
Hello Ryan,

First I would like to apologize for your bad experience as we at the Gold Coast pride ourselves on service and quality. For our burgers we cook them all medium-well unless otherwise and I have notified the cooks in regards to your order. If you want you can notify our cashiers what temperature you would like it specifically. In regards to the tissues we keep them next to our cashiers to control the supply to our customers only and not for any by standers. As well for the price we try our best to stay competitive however due to inflation and high food cost we are trying to remain a profitable business while not being too expensive. I hope you can understand and next time you do stop by please ask for the manager so we are able to discount your next meal and hope to serve you better. Thank you! 

Samir Ibrahim

title: Gold Coast Grill & Catering
text: The bbq bacon cheeseburger is honestly so good! I tell all my friends about it! And the cashier is AMAZINGG! Love her!

title: Gold Coast Grill & Catering
text:
Reasonably priced self-serve food bar and made-to-order menu items.

This restaurant in the Cesar Chavez Student Center at SFSU has a large selection of sandwiches and egg dishes, as well as a self-serve food bar. The made-to-order items usually take five to ten minutes. However, a broccoli and cheese baked potato I ordered took twelve minutes, but it was a big spud. The prices for the self-service food bar are calculated by weight (currently $9.75/lb), so you can have as much or as little of the food you want and pay proportionally. They have shrimp, if you're looking to get more value. In my opinion, most of the food is good. I hear their sandwiches are fantastic, so I'll give them a try next time. Service was good. Utensils and napkins were provided. Seating and restrooms were available nearby. Overall, this is a good place to stop for an inexpensive meal.
name: Neal

title: Gold Coast Grill & Catering
text: I’m glad they are re-opened again. However, $3 extra for a Beyond burger is outrageous. They also stopped serving breakfast all day, which I really miss. I also miss fountain drinks with ice. I would give 2 stars but I gave 3 because I like that they have stamp cards now.
name: Joe Greene
responseFromOwnerText:
Hello Joe,

Thank you for taking the time to leave us a feedback. Unfortunately beyond burgers are more expensive because food cost has gone up significantly since Covid but we continue to maintain keeping our prices as friendly as possible during these times. Also we will have the fountain machine back once we are 100% back which we hope is by beginning of next year. Thank you and we hope you enjoyed your meal!

title: Geneva Steak
text:
Great no frills steak house in the neighborhood.

Very simple but to the point menu.

Asked for a very rare steak, came through and was well seasoned and of good quality.

2 steak meals with beer is $60, which is a great value!

Interior design is humble and welcoming. Feels like you are transported to a movie set in the early 70s or 80s.

My only notes: drafts appear to be misaligned. Beer tasted a little flat.

Would definitely come here again, and recommend others to try it too.

title: Geneva Steak
text: Right on the corner of Mission and Geneva I found Geneva Steak. I walked into the dining room and looking at the seating reminded me of a classic restaurant with red leather booths all around.  I look at the menu on the wall and went for the French Burger, the order included a green salad and my choice of baked potato or rice pilaf. The burger was cooked fresh to order and while my order was being prepared I started with the salad, fresh iceberg lettuce, sliced carrots, red onions, peppers, tomatoes and ranch dressing, the French Burger came soon after, the plate was served by the Chef, a rectangular large bun that was soft and expertly toasted on the grill, usual burger setup, and the baked potato was split in half with melted butter on top. I was happy with the quality of the ingredients definitely a bargain for $13.99. The restaurant specializes on steaks, kabobs and bbq chicken. They have a selection of soft drinks, beers on tap, bottle beer. The place was clean and nice service all around.
name: Salvadorian

title: Geneva Steak

text: I have never been treated so rudely at a restaurant before. I mean WOW! I mentioned we were there for a couple of slices to which he replied (cutting me off) "Only whole pies if dining in." The way he said it though...there was a guy tossing pizza dough standing behind him who just creepily stared at us. They both looked at us like we were some type of stain they both didn't want to bother with. I wouldn't ve had a problem ordering a whole pizza and taking the rest home had he said it in a nicer manner. We thanked him and left in awe. I've dined here many times both alone and with a large group but I will make it a point NOT to come back here again and will let my friends in on my latest experience here. Shame on you Little Joes, the way you treat costumers is pathetic.There are plenty of other restaurants around who are friendly and accommodating AND are far more deserving of my money.

text: Food was great but service and atmosphere I was really disappointed in! The cashier let us stare at the Today’s specials forever before she showed us there was a menu. We dined in and took a number placard only to find out we had to get back up to get our food. The whole vibe of the restaurant just seemed empty and a lack of energy.

title: Pakwan Restaurant
text: I ordered in person and dined in, and when my order of chicken biryani was announced ready to pick up, I was shocked by the size of this dish. The plate was heaped over. Even better was the fact there were chunks of chicken throughout the dish. The large portion size for the price point is an excellent value. The interior is nice, clean, and minimalistic. There is plenty of seating for dining in, but it's also conveniently located for takeout, as there is plenty of street parking.

title: Pakwan Restaurant

인도음식과 파키스탄음식은 거의유사한 느낌, Pakwan은 음식재료를 아끼지않고 향신료도 풍부하여 오랫만에 맛있는 커리를 먹을수있었슴.
서비스수준의 별로 기대하지 않는것이 좋을듯, 팁수순은 높음 ㅜㅜ.

textTranslated:
Indian food and Pakistani food feel almost similar, and Pakwan doesn't skimp on ingredients and has plenty of spices, so it was the first time in a long time that I was able to eat delicious curry.
It would be best not to expect much in terms of service level, but the tipping order is high ㅜㅜ.

title: Pakwan Restaurant

title: Buffalo Kitchen
text:
From 3:00 to 7:00 p.m. there is a 3 entree deal for $31. It could feed a family quite well or have enough for a few meals. I have gotten this three times so far, trying different things each time. They also give me a container of their soup of the day (think broth with some meat and greens,) and a container with rice.

So filling! Also the order comes out pretty quickly. I have not called in yet but it only takes about 10 to 15 minutes for them to fix up your order. There is indoor seating but I haven't seen too many people sit inside, I imagine they have more takeout than anything.

Did you not serve alcohol like most Chinese eateries. I only included this because I overheard a patron asking if there was beer.

If you are in the area stop by and try it out! It isn't bougie. I would say it's not too healthy but oh so delicious. If you are taking public transportation the 8/8bx and 9/9r run along Sunnydale and Visitacion and both stop at Arleta, just a few blocks away.

title: San Marcos Restaurant
text: A fantastic little hole in the wall, hidden gem, honestly one of the highlights of our brief stay in Daly City. We both had the vegetarian burrito (beans rice and cheese) and it was like $6.45 or something outrageously affordable. The portion size was fantastic, and it game with chops and salsa. I've traveled all over California and this was one of the top two best burritos I've had in the state. I can't say enough good things about how delicious it was, and how kind and friendly the staff was. More people need to know about this incredible restaurant!!
name: Levi Smith

title: San Marcos Restaurant
text: NOTE: this restaurant is also know as El Sabor online. No frills little dive place. Excellent food and great customer service. We got the carna asada super and al pastor super burritos. Meat was good quality, beans were obviously home made, and they did  the burritos “El dorado” style, where they finish the burrito on the grill so the shell has a little char/smokiness to it. So good. Salsas homemade and had lots of flavor with a good kick. This place is across the street from our fav Vietnamese soup place, Pho Leun Fat, bonus for us when family is divided on what to get for dinner. Everyone wins!  :)
name: susie mui-shonk

text: Ordered the hand pulled noodles with brown sauce, potstickers, hot & sour soup and wide rice noodle salad. The entire meal was inedible. Literally gloppy, greasy and tasteless. It might have been they were getting ready for vacation as the sign posted on the door stated they'd be closed for New Year's....and wanted to get rid of items on hand....whatever the problem, I do not believe I will give it a second try....it was THAT bad....gave service 3 stars because I was the only order and customer (the entire restaurant was empty and extremely COLD) and had to WAIT after driving across town....

You essentially eat alone and for me it makes the vibes off and they got boxes everywhere on the service counter for some reason.

text: A los dueños de este restaurante quiero pedir su ayuda para que el personal de trabajo .no se vurlen de las personas que llegan independientemente de cualquier religion q tengan.ayer hubo un momento incomodo con burla y bulling .cuando entramos a su restaurante incluyendo una pareja q estaba ayi comiendo. y esa persona q hera un hombre nos dijo q nos fuéramos y dijo una palabra bulgar. entiendo q no tengan control de ellos pero no deberían permitir q su personal participe de eso.y creo el hombre no era el dueño.y aparte si no le gusta ver jente decente .no debería de ir a un lugar donde va toda clase de personas. Si estaba cerrado uvieran puesto el rotulo q dise cerrado .no q se ponen a Reir de  las personas eso no esta bien .y el restaurante queda muy mal .y luego con sus hijos y eso es lo que aprenden los niños por eso esta el mundo asi.espero tomen cartas sobre este asunto
name: Maria Cruz
textTranslated: I want to ask the owners of this restaurant for your help so that the work staff does not abuse the people who arrive regardless of any religion they have. Yesterday there was an uncomfortable moment with mockery and bullying. When we entered their restaurant, including a couple I was there eating. and that person who was a man told us to leave and said a Bulgarian word. I understand that they do not have control over them but they should not allow their staff to participate in that. And I believe the man was not the owner. And besides, if he does not like to see decent people, he should not go to a place where all kinds of people go. . If it was closed, they would have put the sign saying closed. No, they start laughing at people, that's not right. And the restaurant looks very bad. And then with their children and that's what children learn, that's why the world is. So, I hope they take action on this matter.

title: Maple SF Restaurant
text: This is the Chinese restaurant of choice for my partner and me, whether takeout or dine-in, they give big portions, and inflation didn't hit too hard here compared to other Chinese restaurants that my family (Chinese-American) used to eat at, so it is more affordable here but still great quality authentic SF-Chinese-American. I'd recommend the Tomato Beef Chow Mein, which is basically how I judge Chinese restaurants in SF (it's historically an SF Chinese-American specialty). You can request thin crispy pan fried noodles for it too, which is my favorite variation. We also really loved the orange chicken, very tasty. We only dined in once, which was our first time, but the waiter was a polite young man.

title: Mexico Tipico
text:
Authentic Mexican, freshly made, fast service and friendly staff.

Walk in place your order, if you’re dining in they’ll give you a # and drop the food off at your table. They normally get you served in 5 minutes or less and are always friendly.

My fav here is the quesabirria which come with two and the birria juice. The meat is always juicy and tender, packed with flavor. The tortilla always has a nice crisp and holds up well to the juices and dipping birria. Dipping birria is perfectly tasty adds great flavor and even more juice. I’d give this item 5/5 stars!

title: Beep's Burgers

They got rid of one of their best dishes, the fried shrimp basket, that really hurt & the last time I had one of their 1/4 pounder burger baskets it tasted so processed. This 'new gen' thing isn't always the best. I sure do miss the old beeps when it was the real Beeps burgers.

Very good lunch specials. Their food is consistently good and the prices are really good. Most times, I get tea with my lunch special. Even when I get a coke, my bill is only $15, including a $2 tip.

Highly recommended, and will continue to return to enjoy the items on the lunch special menu. They close at 3pm Monday through Saturday. They are closed on Sundays.

Please be patient with the staff and remember to tip kindly...

title: Chef Hunan
text: This is a mystery place that looks super old with really good affordable Chinese food but no one except locals seem to go to. Anything fried, they do exceptionally really really well. Their fried rice is top quality and their ingredients are fresh. You can tell everything is freshly made. Ok so the dine in experience isn't the best. Their rundown indoor and table almost look like it could be dirty but they are not. You get a fresh pot of tea even if you dine alone and not many places in SF you can dine in for lunch under $15 that actually has food you want to eat. Oh forgot to mention their chili oil. Don't know it's in house or bought but it's so good. Not brunt and clear deep red with just the right amount of heat and flavor. Recommend.
name: Hanim Lim

title: Chef Hunan

We came here because our regular place was closed. Glad we did, it had been years. The food was very clean, minimal oil used so flavors really came out. Nothing fancy just solid Chinese American fare. We had Walnut

I knocked over my water doing this, and she acted annoyed.  Never offered more water.  Didn’t offer a receipt after I paid for my meal. title: Tennessee Grill
text: I’m giving the Tennessee Grill five stars, which seems like a lot, because it earns five stars for being very good at what it is. It’s an old-fashioned neighborhood diner with few frills, reasonable prices and excellent service. It’s not the kind of place you’d go out of your way for, but it’s a fine destination.  Full of locals who appreciate a place in which they can linger over coffee and a newspaper or visit with friends. It’s NOT trendy, you won’t be rushed or feel underdressed (as if). The City hasn’t got many of these kinds of places left. Appreciate the Tennessee Grill for what it is.
name: Colin M Mather

title: Tennessee Grill
text:
I've been to this establishment numerous times. It is a staple and a value landmark in the district.

With its  "Mom & Pop" vibe, this place never disappoints any appetite. I enjoy going there every time, when I'm in the area.
name: Ed M Miles

title: Tennessee Grill
text:
You can tell this is a place that the locals go to!! Quick service, nice comfort food, and great pricing.  It gives me that old-school dinner feel, and its actually an SF historic restaurant.

Parking is a bit challenging, but well worth finding a spot.
name: Tiffany Crossley

title: Tennessee Grill
text: Classic
name: Alex Maddox

title: Tennessee Grill
text: A breakfast place that rivals IHOP, with even more delicious pancakes. Perhaps taking feedback from the reviews, it’s filled with a rich buttery aroma. I can’t wait to go back.
name: XW

title: Tennessee Grill
text: All around great place !!
name: William Pecknold

title: Tennessee Grill
text:
We came here for breakfast on Saturday morning and this place was pretty packed but no waiting as it was a largely spaced restaurants.  I liked that most customers appeared local and groups of families. We ordered Irish breakfast, breakfast specials and waffles.  Irish breakfast was pretty good which had Irish bangers and other types of sausages that tasted like blood sausage .   The hash browned seemed a little undercooked.  Overall I felt that their savory breakfast was decent but the sweet breakfast such as pancakes and waffle were just ok .  They were mostly dry and floury , even adding syrup didn’t make it better.
I would definitely try for lunch and diner as the price seems to be reasonable.
name: Grace Kim
